commit_message:
Limit libvirt Nova calls to the local compute node

On OpenStack deployments with an excess of 1,000 provisioned
VMs, the libvirt plugin may not publish metrics for some or
all of the hosted VMs on each compute node.  This is due to
the default osapi_max_limit of 1000, limiting the number of
results from a Nova API query.

Instead of loading instance data for all Nova VMs, this change
limits the query to just VMs hosted on the local compute node.  It
assumes the hostname in agent.yaml matches the hostname in used by
Nova in OS-EXT-SRV-ATTR:host.

Change-Id: Id18abebc550f5bffed553248088f56d5b8a9bb63

commit_message:
Add puppet hook option for --tags

Using --tags allows you to run a puppet manifest and only apply
a subset of the catalog. You can specify --tags package for
example to only install packages resources for a given
manifest.

The intent is to use this option alongside of the TripleO docker
work to selectively control what parts of a puppet manifest
get executed in a container.

Change-Id: Ic8b54c89e62cbe5074f256e29e10f59aa2ab0aae

commit_message:
Create Heat Domain with Keystone_domain resource

 This patch replaces the usage of Exec to create the Heat domain, by
 using the Keystone_domain resource recently implemented in
 puppet-keystone.

cherry picked from Upstream commit: 3ced80f)

Change-Id: I8cd5af772867dfe00a131b119e12800a8e2ec021
Closes-Bug: #1484066

commit_message:
Refactors utils into specific folders

Groups specific utils into more specific folders, so it is more
clear and organised.

Folders:
compute
- livemigrationutils.py
- rdpconsoleutils.py
- rdpconsoleutilsv2.py
- vmutils.py
- vmutilsv2.py

io
- ioutils.py

network
- networkutils.py
- networkutilsv2.py

storage
- basevolumeutils.py
- vhdutils.py
- vhdutilsv2.py
- volumeutils.py
- volumeutilsv2.py

The rest of the utils modules remained where they were.
Moves the module unit tests to reflect the new folder structure.
Updates all the necessary imports.

Change-Id: Ib9e67c93e0de71583fb6477bcd56f39f82eeedec

commit_message:
Revert "Set owner to root for ipsec.secrets for LibreSwan"

This reverts commit fed1a9b92778df4e65bbe03976573d2c82f94163.

Adding chown to the list of approved commands that rootwrap can run makes it trivial to SUID something and create a root shell, among other mischief.

Change-Id: I9e87a4441b01eb5239a24e971eb3474687a8f208

commit_message:
Improving node group templates validation

* Enabling node group templates update validation
  if plugin_name is not updated
* Adding check for volumes_size parameter if
  volumes_per_node is specified
* Adding ability to change plugin version without
  changing a plugin

Closes-Bug: #1494730
Partially-bug: #1494728

Change-Id: If6db35611e5b1501ca6485d0f40bb6c3b65561b8

commit_message:
Formatting and mounting methods changed for ironic

Currently only cinder volumes can be formatted and mounted.
This patch provides an ability of formatting and mounting
any attached storage devices. Also storage_paths method was
moved from node group objects to instance and corresponding
fixes in plugins was made.

Closes-bug: #1478899
Closes-bug: #1478904

Change-Id: If92d6fdea25e374d6d5c404be5ac3677cb60c057

commit_message:
Update hypervisor version

Updated hypervisor version to 8 (integer) rather than the string
value previosly ('710'). Only the major version value is reported
because conductor enforces the source host for a live migration
be less than or equal to the destination host version.  PowerVM
uses capability flags to determine if migration between hosts
is valid rather than comparing version levels.

Closes-Bug: #1498100
Change-Id: Iff53df8d933f2aff9662dee7083becab2a195510

commit_message:
Adds labels support to baymodels

Adds labels to the following:
  1. api baymodel attribute
  2. conductor template definitions and entrypoints
  3. a new column to the baymodel db
  4. objects. Note: Updates baymodel object version
  5. Tests

Partially-Implements: blueprint extend-api-network-attributes
Partially-Implements: blueprint extend-baymodel-net-attributes
Partially-Implements: blueprint conductor-template-net-update

Change-Id: I49f9c7df28f806cdedb3a382b1cb41bc48ff4e90

commit_message:
Make pagination tolerate a deleted marker

Currently, Nova does not paginate correctly if the marker is
a deleted server. When trying to get servers with such a
marker, a "BadRequest" error saying that the marker is
not found will be raised.

We now always pass read_deleted=yes if a marker is being used.

Change-Id: I79a1fb79a38ac4006db622590574308aafdcb5b5
Closes-bug: #1481812
Related-Bug: #1398086
(cherry picked from commit 901c223f351310b38fa17aa1c3dcd758ce897e5e)

commit_message:
Add if_exists arg to all update/delete commands in ovsdb/commands.py

This patch adds the optional arg if_exists=True to ovsdb commands
LSwitchSetExternalIdCommand and SetLogicalPortCommand. This is needed
to avoid raising a RuntimeError exception if a resource is being updated
after it has been deleted due to a concurrent operation.

Depends-on: I3b9f513308d90874ac8e8a7f6345697978d4920f
Change-Id: Ic7493571a944c7698bc2aa5ac92eb584842c44b4

commit_message:
Add fancy pypi version and download images

This patch adds the simple pypi based version icon/image and
download icon/image that's clickable.  This is rendered on shown
on the pypi main page for the version.  An example of what it looks
like is here:

https://pypi.python.org/pypi/oslo.concurrency

Change-Id: I4a10865145cc6f4a16f1e2ae5f9426512e461c2a

That's why we have a good team here :)"}, {'account_id': 3098, 'date': '2015-09-17 15:15:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-09-18 17:31:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I agree with Paul's general sentiment that we need to stop changing things for the sake of changing things :)  Although I agree with Martin that this is a config file and needs to go in the etc directory.  Now is a good time to move things around, as after Liberty operators will expect us to follow a deprecation policy.

 I don't see a strong rationale for renaming the config file from build.ini, I think build.ini is a perfectly reasonable name, and source-location.conf is not as obvious and is too long hence the reason for the -1.  I would be in support of the name build.conf as well.

I like Sam would like to see this change sit in the queue for a few days until folks have had a chance to see it and inspire other changes of this style (config files go to etc) be made now rather then later.

For our config files, we should generate a reference document of where *all* the config files are stored in the deployment and their purpose.  Martin, would you be willing to take that on?  (document what goes in /etc/kolla in a new rst file in a new patch?)

Regards,

-steve"}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-09-18 17:32:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Consolidate kolla-build configuration in one file

The source location definition previously in build.ini was merged in
etc/kolla/kolla-build.conf since it is really configuration for the
kolla-build tool.

Change-Id: I7531af0029bdfeabbaefb8a6aa97b70bb12c021a
Closes-Bug: #1496702

[{'account_id': 360, 'date': '2015-07-27 11:52:54.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 360, 'date': '2015-07-27 12:00:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow-1

Seeing an issue in testing this locally on the controller nodes that use network isolation. Those roles, when using network isolation, move the default route from the ctlplane to the external network. There seems to be some sort of race which causes a momentary network outage after os-net-config has returned. This causes a subsequent Heat notification to fail. Need to investigate this a bit further and post a possible modification to os-net-config to perhaps block on some network operation. It is worth noting that adding a simple sleep 10 after my os-net-config runs fixed this issue (which further indicates we need to block on something in os-net-config that we are not).

Posting now to see what CI says.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-07-27 12:04:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-07-27 11:52:54.000000000', 'message': 'Configure ctlplane network with a static IP

This patch updates all network configuration templates so that
we configure the ctlplane network interface with a static IP
instead of using DHCP.

The IP address used for the static IP is passed into each
nested stack network configuration template via the ControlPlaneIp
parameter.

Two new nested stack parameters called ControlPlaneSubnetCidr and
ControlPlaneDefaultRoute have been added to help configure the CIDR
and default route on the ctlplane. These parameters can be customized
via the parameter_defaults section in the heat environment.

Change-Id: Ib267e6dcf2d5ff77f7a82ee20a123965c2d07565
'}, {'created': '2015-07-29 11:12:51.000000000', 'message': 'Configure ctlplane network with a static IP

This patch updates all network configuration templates so that
we configure the ctlplane network interface with a static IP
instead of using DHCP.

The IP address used for the static IP is passed into each
nested stack network configuration template via the ControlPlaneIp
parameter.

Two new nested stack parameters called ControlPlaneSubnetCidr and
ControlPlaneDefaultRoute have been added to help configure the CIDR
and default route on the ctlplane. These parameters can be customized
via the parameter_defaults section in the heat environment.

A single new template called net-config-static-bridge.yaml has
been added to help migrate towards using the static
configuration templates.

Change-Id: Ib267e6dcf2d5ff77f7a82ee20a123965c2d07565
'}, {'created': '2015-08-16 23:14:49.000000000', 'message': 'Configure ctlplane network with a static IP

This patch updates all network configuration templates so that
we configure the ctlplane network interface with a static IP
instead of using DHCP.

The IP address used for the static IP is passed into each
nested stack network configuration template via the ControlPlaneIp
parameter.

Three new nested stack parameters called ControlPlaneSubnetCidr,
ControlPlaneDefaultRoute, and EC2MetadataIp have been added to help
configure the CIDR, default route, and EC2 metadata route on the ctlplane
statically.  These parameters can be customized via the
parameter_defaults section in the heat environment.

A single new template called net-config-static-bridge.yaml has

commit_message:
Configure ctlplane network with a static IP

This patch updates all network configuration templates so that
we configure the ctlplane network interface with a static IP
instead of using DHCP.

The IP address used for the static IP is passed into each
nested stack network configuration template via the ControlPlaneIp
parameter.

Three new nested stack parameters called ControlPlaneSubnetCidr,
ControlPlaneDefaultRoute, and EC2MetadataIp have been added to help
configure the CIDR, default route, and EC2 metadata route on the ctlplane
statically.  These parameters can be customized via the
parameter_defaults section in the heat environment.

A single new template called net-config-static-bridge.yaml has
been added to help migrate towards using the static
configuration templates when not using network isolation.

Depends-On: I257e1cba6dee16f73f75512d1284e1e3b9d4c831

Change-Id: Ib267e6dcf2d5ff77f7a82ee20a123965c2d07565

commit_message:
Enable eventing from system

This change set allows for the PowerVM agents to listen to events from
the system and provision a port based off of an event in the system.

The original support to listen to ports from Neutron is still enabled.
However, the length of time that it waits is now dramatically reduced as
the system events themselves will also be considered.

Change-Id: I0d728e3f502800773cb2dc61cc6561638ecd7abe

commit_message:
Use a standard hostname to prevent setting invalid hostnames.

It's possible for a tenant to change their router's name to something that's
not a valid hostname.  This uses a standard ak-<tenant-uuid> value that we can
rely on.

Change-Id: Id64f7c796f8ef01200f51494611458b5731149c8
Fixes-bug: #1496848
(cherry picked from commit 760df4839ef2f97a6825f852b87556569c6c03c7)

commit_message:
devstack: Remove ovs during unstack.

The networking-ovn devstack plugin installs the latest ovs from source
to get ovn installed.  This makes unstack uninstall it so it isn't
accidentally left around if someone tries to go re-install ovs from
the distro package later.

Change-Id: I66f0f3f9ab64b188fadc8d74fe16ad7e07c5e3e6
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Make is so exceptions have some message

If you don't have a message on an exception it prints out as
nothing.  This change will default the messaqge to the class
name which should be useful.

Change-Id: Ie246b37c971e8c30752714b49aa55e69482b32e7

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-08-05 23:42:24.000000000', 'message': "Add ARP spoofing protection for LinuxBridge agent

This patch adds ARP spoofing protection for the Linux Bridge
agent based on ebtables. This code was written to be minimally
invasive with the intent of back-porting to Kilo.

The protection is enabled and disabled with the same
'prevent_arp_spoofing' agent config flag added for the OVS agent
in I7c079b779245a0af6bc793564fa8a560e4226afe.

The protection works by setting up an ebtables chain for each port
and jumping all ARP traffic to that chain. The port-specific chains
have a default DROP policy and then have allow rules installed that
only allow ARP traffic with a source CIDR that matches one of the
port's fixed IPs or an allowed address pair.

Since this is a back-port to Kilo, it is disabled by default just
like the protection added for OVS.

Conflicts:
	neutron/plugins/linuxbridge/agent/linuxbridge_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/plugins/linuxbridge/common/config.py
	neutron/tests/common/machine_fixtures.py

Closes-Bug: #1274034
Change-Id: I0b0e3b1272472385dff060897ecbd25e93fd78e7
(cherry picked from commit 04197bc4bbf2bc611371060db839028c2686f87a)

commit_message:
Add ARP spoofing protection for LinuxBridge agent

This patch adds ARP spoofing protection for the Linux Bridge
agent based on ebtables. This code was written to be minimally
invasive with the intent of back-porting to Kilo.

The protection is enabled and disabled with the same
'prevent_arp_spoofing' agent config flag added for the OVS agent
in I7c079b779245a0af6bc793564fa8a560e4226afe.

The protection works by setting up an ebtables chain for each port
and jumping all ARP traffic to that chain. The port-specific chains
have a default DROP policy and then have allow rules installed that
only allow ARP traffic with a source CIDR that matches one of the
port's fixed IPs or an allowed address pair.

Since this is a back-port to Kilo, it is disabled by default just
like the protection added for OVS.

This patch additionally pulls back the required ebtables filter and
the functional test helpers to support the tests.

Conflicts:
	neutron/plugins/linuxbridge/agent/linuxbridge_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/plugins/linuxbridge/common/config.py
	neutron/tests/common/machine_fixtures.py

Closes-Bug: #1274034
Change-Id: I0b0e3b1272472385dff060897ecbd25e93fd78e7
(cherry picked from commit 04197bc4bbf2bc611371060db839028c2686f87a)

commit_message:
Add configurable options for HA networks

The L3 HA mechanism creates a project network for HA (VRRP) traffic
among routers. The HA project network uses the first (default) network
type in 'tenant_network_types'. Depending on the environment, this
combination may not provide a desirable path for HA traffic. For
example, some operators may prefer to use a specific network for HA
traffic to prevent split-brain issues.

This patch adds configurable options that target the network_type and
the physical_network of the created HA network.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1481443
Change-Id: I3527a780179b5982d6e0eb0b8c32d6dafeeab730
(cherry picked from commit 98618644ce3c36eabfcc0aea49e7962b0506a567)
Conflicts:
	etc/neutron.conf

To garyk,

As I described in my Commit Message and bug#1293540, there is some condition that neutron will remove the bridge and interface it created.

In that circumstance, if we resume a VM, an exception "libvirt error, can't get the bridge MTU" will occur since the VM cannot find the bridge any more.

Therefore, in this patch, we call the "plug_vif" method before resume the VM, and "plug_vif" method needs "network_info" as its parameter.'}, {'account_id': 2733, 'date': '2015-03-22 18:51:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

gary - when you do a "nova image-create", nova removes the tap device for a while. The linuxbridge agent detects this and processes the device removed as usual. But if was the last tap on the bridge, it also removes the empty bridge - maybe it shouldn't do that. https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blame/master/neutron/plugins/linuxbridge/agent/linuxbridge_neutron_agent.py#L917'}, {'account_id': 13630, 'date': '2015-03-23 02:05:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 11.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-03-23 02:56:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11: Verified+1

This problem is broader than just snapshot. commit_message:
Ensure bridge exists before resuming a VM after an offline snapshot

If we take a cold snapshot of a local instance and only one instance
on the host, neutron (only occurs when we use neutron linuxbridge)
would delete the bridge after nova called the libvirt function
'managedSave'.

Therefore, when this instance is resuming after cold snapshot is done,
it may raise an exception "libvirt error, can't get the bridge MTU".

In this patch, we re-plug the vif for the instance before resuming it.

And since nova image-create and nova shelve also involve the operation
of doing snapshot, this patch deal with them too.

Change-Id: I43fd09c6c36aa401b53a1af77fcb6775313797c1
Closes-Bug: #1293540

commit_message:
Start using keystoneauth for keystone sessions

This is being split out from keystoneclient. That's a happymaking.
In order to make this work, we also need to fix glance image data upload
for v2 put. It seems that the internal interface has changed. Pass the file
object and not a size. We could do the work to figure out how to do it
in two discreet steps, but I believe that would involved a chunk of
engineering on a dead interface and is not worth it.

Also, Change ignore-errors to ignore_errors

Change-Id: I816752f8f4d29e40d41622bd8a271eb5c8e5a9fb

commit_message:
Change hypervisor_version to numeric value

hypervisor_version should be represented in numeric value for
comparison purpose. This is particular important during migration
since we cannot migrate from a host with hypervisor_version
higher than the destination host.

Change-Id: I440b0e1ffe9a4798c738bc4d9d1806639c8cad42
Closes-Bug: #1498100

commit_message:
adds the config_template to nova

The change modifies the nova template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I9842ed3fcb2cc4aa379a582359b1ca5d0747f714

commit_message:
adds the config_template to neutron

The change modifies the neutron template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: Ia9e4acdb86c1c61db182771658d6a175a4c45b38

* change auth_for_proxy_user to auth_for_proxy
* adding tests for swift client to exercise logic

commit_message:
Adding fake plugin usage in validation ut

Currently vanilla plugin is used for validation tests
and every deprecation of vanilla plugin leads to
validation tests update. It could be avoided if fake
plugin would be used.

Change-Id: I63fe61ce35c15e699033a4a8c3bb61bd571f68de
Closes-bug: #1495944

commit_message:
HDP plugin should ignore untagged configs when creating cluster_spec

The HDP plugin generates an operational object for provisioning
and managing clusters.  This object should ignore configuration
parameters that did not originate in ambari-config-resource.json
and hence have no tag value.

Change-Id: Ie6d6387a4595f7cde0ca90fdef5efff27a78a858
Closes-bug: #1496970

commit_message:
Fixes for python3.4 support

- Removed yasfb from requirements (no longer needed, not py3 compat)
- Changed iops calculation to be compatible with py3 division changes

Change-Id: Ic8a53562be401deaa391d21b5ff6f92ffa7d07d3

commit_message:
Bump diskimage-builder upper constraint to 1.1.2

This release contains a number of important fixes for ironic-agent
element. One of them is required for building ironic-agent on Fedora.

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-09-15 23:27:30.000000000', 'message': "Add total cell/socket/core/thread counts to cpu_info

Rather than leave it up to clients to do a bunch of math to figure
out the socket/core/etc. counts based on some odd breadcrumbs, roll
up totals for all of that and present it with the cpu_info attribute.
This has the side-benefit of giving accurate counts on asymmetric
NUMA machines with no extra client effort required.

But for people that like doing that kind of thing, also include the
number of NUMA cells in the cpu_info['topology'] attribute.

Change-Id: I945f32bce96f27939d39b86af6ccec73b754f886
Closes-Bug: 1156456
"}, {'created': '2015-09-16 22:04:21.000000000', 'message': "Add NUMA cell count to cpu_info

Adds the number of NUMA cells from libvirt to the cpu_info['topology']
attribute, so that clients using that data for socket/core/thread
counting on hypervisors can get better-quality results.

Closes-Bug: 1156456
Change-Id: I945f32bce96f27939d39b86af6ccec73b754f886
"}, {'created': '2015-09-16 22:12:47.000000000', 'message': "libvirt: Add NUMA cell count to cpu_info

Adds the number of NUMA cells from libvirt to the cpu_info['topology']
attribute, so that clients using that data for socket/core/thread
counting on hypervisors can get better-quality results.

Closes-Bug: 1156456
Change-Id: I945f32bce96f27939d39b86af6ccec73b754f886
"}]
commit_message:
libvirt: Add NUMA cell count to cpu_info

Adds the number of NUMA cells from libvirt to the cpu_info['topology']
attribute, so that clients using that data for socket/core/thread
counting on hypervisors can get better-quality results.

Closes-Bug: 1156456
Change-Id: I945f32bce96f27939d39b86af6ccec73b754f886

commit_message:
Combine exit codes of the two functional test runs

The script was only returning the exit code of the second of the
two test runs.  With this change, a failure of either either run
will correctly be reported as an error.

Change-Id: I81766dee2ac141ceddf683b50a2aef11a79f968b
Closes-bug: #1488693

commit_message:
[COVERAGE] Turn off coverage

We need to fix .coveragerc and turn off coverage in one patch, since
cover.sh scrip launch check for previous patch which contain uncompatible
with coverage 4.0 option.

Also, fix for floating bug is required.

Change-Id: I4cc49c01bc5bb633f08353762f963cb4343fc6cb
Partial-Bug: #1497897

[{'created': '2015-08-13 17:05:18.000000000', 'message': 'Cleanup some bash comparisions

Use "=" instead of "==" for normal tests to conform with POSIX.
Use -eq if the right side is a numeric value.

Change-Id: Id40a560e3cf2faf8a14a1533c3a31f145796fd67
'}, {'created': '2015-08-18 04:28:15.000000000', 'message': 'Cleanup some bash comparisions

Use "=" instead of "==" for normal tests to conform with POSIX.
Use -eq if the right side is a numeric value.
Use [] instead of [[]] if appropriate.

Change-Id: Id40a560e3cf2faf8a14a1533c3a31f145796fd67
'}, {'created': '2015-08-18 04:33:41.000000000', 'message': 'Cleanup some bash comparisions

Use "=" instead of "==" for normal tests to conform with POSIX,
use -z in cases it's comparison against "". Replace [[]] where
not needed with [].

Change-Id: Id40a560e3cf2faf8a14a1533c3a31f145796fd67
'}]
commit_message:
Cleanup some bash comparisions

Use "=" instead of "==" for normal tests to conform with POSIX,
use -z in cases it's comparison against "". Replace [[]] where
not needed with [].

Change-Id: Id40a560e3cf2faf8a14a1533c3a31f145796fd67

commit_message:
Fix race between resource audit and cpu pinning

This fixes a race between the claimed CPUs of an instance being
persisted to the DB, and the resource audit scanning the DB for
instances and subtracting pinned CPUs from the list of available CPUs.

The problem only shows up when the following sequence happens:
1) instance A (with dedicated cpus) boots on a compute node
2) resource audit runs on that compute node
3) instance B (with dedicated cpus) boots on the same compute node

The bug is that the claimed numa topology isn't updated until
after we release COMPUTE_RESOURCES_SEMAPHORE, so when the resource
audit retrieves the list of instances the numa_topology hasn't
been updated yet for the most recent one.

The fix is to persist the claimed numa topology before releasing
COMPUTE_RESOURCES_SEMAPHORE.

Closes-Bug: #1454451
Co-Authored-By: Dan Smith <dansmith@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit 2427d288bc017a5b91430ffe16419d47703d2060)

Conflicts:
	nova/compute/manager.py
	nova/tests/unit/compute/test_resource_tracker.py
	nova/tests/unit/compute/test_tracker.py

Change-Id: I553f2e43a68577c83d890c3671380af68f9e725a

tests as a mock function's parameters got changed.

commit_message:
api: add default_floating_pool parameter

default_floating_pool is an parameter used by nova api to talk to
neutron server and associate floating IP to servers from the public
network. Upstream default is 'nova', let's keep it but at least this
patch allows to change the parameter.

Change-Id: Ic060fc18c8f5d7dc8fcf1d7bd921623dc505a515

When creating Cinder::Type resources, we need to make sure Keystone
resources for Cinder are created, because they'll be used by

commit_message:
Make sure cinder is created before creating Cinder::Type

When creating Cinder::Type resources, we need to make sure Keystone
resources for Cinder are created, because they'll be used by
Cinder::Type to create a volume type.

This patch is useful when Cinder::Type is declared on the same node as
Cinder API & Keystone server.

Change-Id: Ia823d80a4eb384ac51d8b1711e8664a3d29247f7

commit_message:
Remove special Zanata suffix from jobs

Now that we are switched to zanata we don't need two sets of job names
to keep the transifex vs zanata split straight in JJB and Zuul. Just
condense down to translation-jobs.

Change-Id: Ic512b2f58a1c9a084f4e25fdf4761fd0c4e6ff0a

commit_message:
Add missing X-xxxx HTTP headers to the unauth context

The unauth context is used by Barbican out of the box for local API evaluation
as well as for deployments where an authenticating proxy (such as Repose) is
placed in front of Barbican. Hence this unauth context must provide all the
required HTTP header settings to the Barbican context prior to policy engine
computation for RBAC and so forth. This CR provides those missing headers.

Change-Id: Ib1d6abdb384f5883aa06ec1b6811c3ad80291568
Closes-Bug: #1497639

Yeh, I saw this a week ago and I was real confused what was going on.  Are you sure this isn't just a identity-api-version issue?  Why would a v2 catalog support v3?"}, {'account_id': 6522, 'date': '2015-05-10 13:52:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

There were multiple reasons,
       - The software should work as expected, the client shouldn't fail horribly
       - Its probably a good idea for the client to be resilient enough to handle changes to support mutiple api versions."}, {'account_id': 8736, 'date': '2015-05-10 14:34:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Wait for some more opinions, but generally, I'm in favor of keeping auth version and identity api version independent.  If that was the case though, the v3 catalog command should support v2 auth.  I think these are the only areas we'd have a problem."}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2015-05-10 23:16:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

So this is really a side effect of mixing the CRUD and auth parts of keystone. You can use a v3 token (with a v3 catalog) to access V2 operations and vice versa so i can see why you want it.

Ideally we would move commands like this to their own top level version independent support.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2015-05-11 18:19:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

I think we do need to head down the road of disconnecting the auth and CRUD versions and this may only be the start of things like this that we need to fix.  Can we start by reconciling the v2 and v3 _format_endpoints() functions into a single function so both v2 and v3 can handle the 'other' version auth as Jamie mentions?  I _think_ that's just moving a unified version of _format_endpoints() into identity.common."}, {'account_id': 6522, 'date': '2015-05-12 22:29:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

If I understand correctly it's agreed that this should be fixed, but the general consensus is the code should be refactored to do so. 

If thats the case then that's out of the scope for this Change and Bug Report. Which I'll close if agreed."}, {'account_id': 6522, 'date': '2015-05-12 22:30:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

commit_message:
Use of ast for integers doesn't changes type

ast.literal_eval doesn't change types for Integer
Booleans resulting in DBAPIError exceptions with
at least postgresql. Boolean columns need to be
explicitly cast to boolean types.

Change-Id: If10be4f6748be3cad48167ba6bbf4433ce9c8abf
Closes-Bug: #1494475

commit_message:
Initialize Database Before Running Quota Enforcer Unit Tests

The database_utils.RepositoryTestCase mixin ensures that the unit
test database is initialized at the start of a test case class.

Change-Id: I087784151a8ad1263b884619eb30079dafc1b89d
Closes-bug: #1497774

commit_message:
Adding validation of workflow graph

 * To avoid circular dependency between mistral.workbook.parser
 and mistral.workflow.commands reserved task names were moved to
 workbook.tasks module.

Closes-Bug: #1494635

Change-Id: I21337a9b616f55c3bbdc957538b25d36246b3903

commit_message:
Modify nova help list message for --tenant

The --all-tenants option does not have impact
when --tenant is used. Help message about
--all-tenants inside the help section of --tenant
creates uncertainty.

Change-Id: Iaddf2370f349c6da712e0096a6ecbcbc61d37836
Closes-Bug: #1497151

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-09-16 16:45:25.000000000', 'message': 'Modifed http_check to init keystone clients and re-use

The previous code was initializing the keystone client each
time check was called in the case use_keystone is True.
Our default http_check config uses drop wizard checks that do
not require keystone.  This could eliminate the number of
keystone token requests for any http_checks that require
a keystone token, since now they will be cached.

Change-Id: I47827d549365c29a36846d51ede0fb06da435ac7
'}]
commit_message:
Modifed http_check to init keystone clients and re-use

The previous code was initializing the keystone client each
time check was called in the case use_keystone is True.
Our default http_check config uses drop wizard checks that do
not require keystone.  This could eliminate the number of
keystone token requests for any http_checks that require
a keystone token, since now they will be cached.

Change-Id: I47827d549365c29a36846d51ede0fb06da435ac7

commit_message:
Cleanup a few auth_token comments

It is not only memcached cases where revocations need to be checked,
so this cleans up an old comment that was no longer giving the full
picture on that. It also corrects a couple other nit grammatical
issues for better clarity.

Change-Id: I51e51d2127c79b11b206e1459f3e83957bf44128

commit_message:
Remove non-Zanata propose jobs

Now that we have switched all projects to pulling translations from
Zanata, as a first step, destroy all the jobs and their related job
groups that are no longer used.

commit_message:
Add password for user cirros in the guide of launch an instance

The guide of launch an instance only mentioned the user name of image
cirros which is 'cirros' and didn`t provide the password of the user
'cirros'.
This commit intend to add password for user 'cirros'.

Closes-Bug: #1497060
Change-Id: I4857141c6e146bb6b9b9ffbbea169097bf4ffc20

TBH I didn't try very hard before moving on to more pressing matters since I deploy on bare metal."}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-09-17 11:53:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Code-Review+2

(1 comment)

From an editing perspective, you have my +2 Martin.  It seems like there is some disagreement over defaults for storage node count and hypervisor type.  Those will require code changes, which I'd recommend doing as new independent patches.  From a "do the docs match the code" the answer is yes, so I recommend filing a couple bugs on the raised points so the docs can be merged.'}, {'account_id': 13039, 'date': '2015-09-17 14:42:03.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

(1 comment)

Steve, it's actually the opposite: VirtualBox works on all major OS, which is not the case for KVM.

Paul, quick question. Does our Vagrantfile work without the Extension Pack? I think it should, I just want to confirm. I do not want to default to non-free software if there is a free alternative available.

Agreed the discussion about the default provider shouldn't block this patch. I'm open to discussion.

For the storage node count, I'm going to add a note to the documentation."}, {'account_id': 13039, 'date': '2015-09-17 14:48:51.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 3098, 'date': '2015-09-17 15:07:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Update tuskar to support renamed heat roles

We are dropping the -puppet from the role templates in
the puppet directory. This change updates 90-tuskar-db-sync
so that it supports either case.

Change-Id: I71cb07b2f5305aaf9c43ab175cca976e844b8175

commit_message:
Expose serial, wwn and vendor on the BlockDevice object

Currently we only use these disk properties for root device hints.
However, they'll be really useful for inspector, especially for also
implementing root device hints.

Change-Id: I48aa6b6d2d198d16f2f8e387970f7230066cf8a2

commit_message:
Remove pip install of pyscss in Horizon

Because of the correction of the dependney repos in RDO, pyscss
no longer needs to be installed via pip.

Change-Id: Ide0a0181a9b1353a043956ab9849a2d261f1c243
Closes-Bug: #1497436

commit_message:
os-net-config: add ping_metadata_ip function

Updates os-net-config to use --detailed-exit-codes so that when
a network change has been detected we can perform a network validation
via a new ping_metadata_ip function. This function performs a simple ping
test back to the IP address of the Heat API which should always be
available after any network configuration change.

The motivation for this change is to allow network configuration
changes time to settle. When making changes to the ctlplane (which
is typically used to contact the undercloud Heat API for subsequent
configuration notifications and updates) it is sometimes desirable to
wait a few seconds before proceeding. This avoids a race where the
ctlplane was switch to a static IP address and the very next
Heat notification would sometimes fail.

Depends-On: I8f22fa15335d1276f4e444a6454a24ff486e1495

Change-Id: I257e1cba6dee16f73f75512d1284e1e3b9d4c831

The Swift configuration item [filter:recon]/recon_lock_path is set to
'/var/lock/swift' by openstack-ansible in the appropriate configuration
files. The playbooks also create the directory if it does not exist. If
the host is rebooted the directory '/var/lock/swift' is missing and must
be recreated.

/var/lock (/run/lock) is a tmpfs and so the directory /var/lock/swift
will not persist between reboots.

Swift attempts to create a directory in the directory specified by

parent directories.

set by Swift, '/var/lock'. This allows it to create the directory
'/var/lock/swift-recon-object-cron'. The creation of '/var/lock/swift'

commit_message:
Change recon_lock_path to /var/lock

The Swift configuration item [filter:recon]/recon_lock_path is set to
'/var/lock/swift' by openstack-ansible in the appropriate configuration
files. The playbooks also create the directory if it does not exist. If
the host is rebooted the directory '/var/lock/swift' is missing and must
be recreated.

/var/lock (/run/lock) is a tmpfs and so the directory /var/lock/swift
will not persist between reboots.

Swift attempts to create a directory in the directory specified by
recon_lock_path however it does not recursively create any missing
parent directories.

This commit changes the value of [filter:recon]/recon_lock_path to that
set by Swift, '/var/lock'. This allows it to create the directory
'/var/lock/swift-recon-object-cron'. The creation of '/var/lock/swift'
is also removed from the playbooks.

i'm going to put -1 because i think we need to discuss expected results.

as i understand it, this will effectively stop the converter from building any events if there is a corresponding '!xyz' entry anywhere in the definition file.

for me, the definition file isn't defining filtering rules but rather is defining whether a certain notification should have index/conversion rules applied to it."}, {'account_id': 13560, 'date': '2015-06-03 22:45:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@gordc: I think the change will allow all events but exclude ones that begin with !

Is there an alternative way to prevent a few events from matching while allowing others? In this case, i am alluding to matching dns.domain.* and excluding dns.record.* events. 

(From http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ceilometer/events.html)
event_type - This is a list (or a string, which will be taken as a 1 element list) of event_types this definition will handle. These can be wildcarded with unix shell glob syntax. An exclusion listing (starting with a ‘!’) will exclude any types listed from matching. If ONLY exclusions are listed, the definition will match anything not matching the exclusions.'}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2015-06-04 12:55:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

@Rohit,

so i see the two event files as such:

event_definitions - defines how to index attributes and build an event model from notification

event_pipeline - filters generated events.

the 'catch_all' option i think is similar to our 'disable_non_metric_meters' option. it's just a trigger that says 'hey, we really should be using this since it probably contains nothing really useful, but i just want to enable it anyways'

i don't know if that logic makes sense to everyone else"}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2015-06-14 17:04:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

Hi,

I think if we have an exclusion option then it shouldn't be possible to overwrite it from another file as it is very confusing. My question here is that what if we remove this option from the definition file and add it to the event pipeline, like how we can filter meters in pipeline.yaml? This way we could control the events collection from one file, which sounds better from usability point of view IMHO.

Best Regards,
Ildiko"}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2015-06-15 01:08:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

@Ildiko,

i considered this when i was implementing the pipeline -- to essentially, move this 'event_definitions' as a 'transformer'. this can still be done but i think we will ultimately always need to have the ability to support exclusion in the definition file.

current workflow:
  receive message -> convert to event (defintion) -> push through pipeline -> publish

we can change it to:
  receive message -> filter through pipeline -> convert to event (definition) -> publish

i think the second case works but you still need to support exlusion in definition in case you want to tranform/index all compute.instance.* messages except one.

the main confusion seems to be that people think the definition file is a filtering file... it is not. it is an indexing/transformation file"}, {'account_id': 13560, 'date': '2015-06-16 00:29:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

gordc: The second approach seems better. I think its optimal to filter events before applying definitions..I thought its possible to specify for exclusion in pipeline as well.'}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2015-06-16 04:00:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

@Rohit, there is a patch to do something similar to the second option here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/178208/'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-08-06 08:01:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change or one of its cross-repo dependencies was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of its repository. Please rebase the change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 13560, 'date': '2015-09-21 16:04:27.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Abandoned since event definitions is not a filter for events..'}]

commit_message:
Fix catch-all event def to exclude !event

Excluding an event using event definitions
gets overriden by the catch-all event def
and doesnt get excluded by default.

This fixes the catch-all (*) event def by
adding any excluded event types to it.

Change-Id: Iee42054d6159c579c80b14268ecaf76cb3929a3c
Closes-Bug: 1460808

commit_message:
Enable block-scoped-var

This rule enforces C-style block scoped variables, which javascript
does not do natively.

http://eslint.org/docs/rules/block-scoped-var

Change-Id: I9969a9c32e90a65fcc998e50e0966402eacfa8bd

subject: Change to a Dynamic Whitelist of Persister Metrics
messages:
[{'account_id': 18179, 'date': '2015-09-16 14:59:24.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 11809, 'date': '2015-09-16 15:23:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

The original metrics give an idea of the actual health of the persister. The only problem is that they are assuming that there are 4 threads. The right answer is to probably read the persister config file to find the number of threads and then pull the right metrics out. Or add some sort of pattern matching so it doesn't have to be an exact match.

commit_message:
Fix for multiple entries in ucast_mac_remote

checking mac and logical switch while creating l2-gateway-connection,
if there is entry in ucast_mac_remote for second l2-gateway-connection for
same logical switch.
taken care of deleting ucast_mac_remote and vlan_bindings
while deleting l2-gateway-connection.

Closes-Bug:1447910

Co-Authored-By: Phani Pawan <ppawan@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: MANJUNATH PATIL <mpatil@hp.com>

Change-Id: Id9205c902210d94d7168eb95fbd6c3520fbb6239
(cherry picked from commit 5d4a4ad7904def80ef13ab0673103cf7be161716)

commit_message:
Fix for internal server error

internal server error occurs if empty l2gateway is passed in
_check_port_fault_status_and_switch_fault_status.so checking the the same.

Closes-Bug: 1454670

Change-Id: I5faba8d5e097b5ca8aeec44b7fde0a61d98486e4
(cherry picked from commit eaf54d893a5332ddd6ab9d747ed13ba5f28c05a3)

package and the neutron plugin config type as this constraint has been

commit_message:
Use a standard hostname to prevent setting invalid hostnames.

It's possible for a tenant to change their router's name to something that's
not a valid hostname.  This uses a standard ak-<tenant-uuid> value that we can
rely on.

Change-Id: Id64f7c796f8ef01200f51494611458b5731149c8
Fixes-bug: #1496848

commit_message:
Ensure CNAME RRSets only have one record

Throw a 400 error back at the user if they try to create a CNAME
RRSet with more than 1 record.

Change-Id: I252fcd046dc902ff28162d831c0c0fd6b0dea3d2
Closes-Bug: 1486743

commit_message:
Create Heat Domain with Keystone_domain resource

 This patch replaces the usage of Exec to create the Heat domain, by
 using the Keystone_domain resource recently implemented in
 puppet-keystone.

cherry picked from Upstream commit: 3ced80f)

Change-Id: I8cd5af772867dfe00a131b119e12800a8e2ec021
Closes-Bug: #1484066

commit_message:
adds the config_template to tempest

The change modifies the tempest template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I3b664fcec14bf01f9916ced0b8595a57d4873f79

commit_message:
Remove unused Node dependencies.

This removes several large and unnecessary node dependencies,
reducing the total space consumed by build dependencies by around
34%. In particular, `gulp-imagemin` and `debowerify` (along with
their associated build steps) are removed, freeing ~200MB.

subject: Disable the _cleanup_incomplete_migrations() periodic task by default
revisions:
[{'created': '2015-09-21 14:52:30.000000000', 'message': "Disable the _cleanup_incomplete_migrations() periodic task by default

This patch disables the incomplete migration cleanup periodic task by
default because it will destroy data if an instance is on shared storage.
If an instance was involved in a failed migration, the task deletes the
instance storage without checking whether it is on shared storage first.
This means that it could delete the one and only copy of an instance's
data because one side of a failed migration ran this task.

Unfortunately, the original code was using an existing configuration
variable for control, to make it backportable. Thus, this patch must add
another variable to split control of the two tasks, so that the offending
one may be disabled by default.

Deployers that do not use shared storage that are concerned about the
security implications of the original bug (1392527) should re-enable
this task on their systems at a reasonable interval. Deployers that are
using shared storage SHOULD NOT ENABLE THIS, but also should  not be
affected by the aforementioned bug either.

This is considered the least amount of change we can make to mitigate
the issue at this point in the release.

decision during initial configuration. It also deserves release note

Partial-Bug: #1498023
"}]
commit_message:
Disable the _cleanup_incomplete_migrations() periodic task by default

This patch disables the incomplete migration cleanup periodic task by
default because it will destroy data if an instance is on shared storage.
If an instance was involved in a failed migration, the task deletes the
instance storage without checking whether it is on shared storage first.
This means that it could delete the one and only copy of an instance's
data because one side of a failed migration ran this task.

Unfortunately, the original code was using an existing configuration
variable for control, to make it backportable. Thus, this patch must add
another variable to split control of the two tasks, so that the offending
one may be disabled by default.

Deployers that do not use shared storage that are concerned about the
security implications of the original bug (1392527) should re-enable
this task on their systems at a reasonable interval. Deployers that are
using shared storage SHOULD NOT ENABLE THIS, but also should  not be
affected by the aforementioned bug either.

This is considered the least amount of change we can make to mitigate
the issue at this point in the release.

DocImpact: This needs explanation for the deployers to make a proper
decision during initial configuration. It also deserves release note
material for people upgrading to this code.

Change-Id: I9f8c26cfb545a56bc5736064ec672e4d76e057d7
Partial-Bug: #1498023

commit_message:
Remove POSIX file modes.

This patch removes File resources, which should be delivered by packaging
tools. These resources (files and directories with attributes) could be in
conflict with different OS packaging systems, which isn't a desired result.

Change-Id: Ife7d6b061380ea5ddcdf581c22e0fa6b1d31da61
Closes-bug: #1458915

According to http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/governance/tree/reference/projects.yaml#n2334 both solum and the client are "release:independent" and not managed by the release team, so you don't need to submit a request for a release here. Let me know if you need some help with the manual release process.'}, {'account_id': 2506, 'date': '2015-09-14 20:16:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Doug,

Thanks for the clarification. I did not realize that Solum service and client both are release:independent, and that means your email [1] is not applicable to us.

About manual release -- yes, we would like to tag a release for liberty in next couple of weeks. Any help with this would be much appreciated. If there is any documentation that outlines the steps, I can check it out.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-September/074367.html

Regards,

Devdatta'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2015-09-14 20:48:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

The tools for managing releases are in the openstack-infra/release-tools repository. For the client library, you want to look at release_postversion.sh. For the service, you might want intermediary.sh or milestone.sh/rccut.sh depending on your release model. Have a look at the README in that repo and then drop by #openstack-relmgr-office on IRC and we can chat about the differences if you have questions.'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2015-09-21 15:11:28.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

I'm going to discard this patch to remove it from the review dashboard. We can discuss whether the solum team wants to have releases managed by the release team during the mitaka cycle between now and the summit."}, {'account_id': 2506, 'date': '2015-09-21 15:14:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Sounds good.

I haven't yet gotten around to following the steps on the links that you have sent. Will reach out when we try them and if we run into any issues.

Thank you for the help."}]

AgentDeploy.tear_down_cleaning into a common place so that it
can be reused for ISCSIDeploy.

and agent_erase_devices_iterations to the group named
'deploy' and deprecates their place in the 'agent' group..

commit_message:
Refactor agent {prepare,tear_down}_cleaning into deploy_utils

This commit refactors code from AgentDeploy.prepare_cleaning and
AgentDeploy.tear_down_cleaning into a common place so that it
can be reused for ISCSIDeploy. It also moves the method
agent.build_agent_options to deploy_utils module.

The following CONF options have been deprecated and renamed:
[agent]agent_erase_devices_priority => [deploy]erase_devices_priority
[agent]agent_erase_devices_iterations => [deploy]erase_devices_iterations

The old CONF options will be removed in the Mitaka release.

Change-Id: I818c9f81f5469bf5029495dc9b65259718c41cd5
Implements: blueprint iscsi-deploy-in-band-cleaning

commit_message:
Rely on autorequire for config resource ordering

Currently we specify the ordering of config resources wherever it is
necessary based on the presence of the file it will write to, or the
presence of the package in charge of providing the file it will write
to.

Those kind of ordering can be specified directly at the resource level
using the autorequire mechanism. With this patch, any config resource
will make sure the package in charge of providing the file will be
installed first.

Change-Id: I73285227e9bbd0c895d9f74bab9e9bb65acaba40

Revert "Fix Sahara installation for Ubuntu"

This commit reverts "Fix Sahara installation for Ubuntu" (I4c9e9206e3e60f3c85224ae120516badb331672e)
because bug 1450945 is duplicate for 1452698 and it was fixed for Liberty.

Related-bug: #1450945
Related-bug: #1452698

commit_message:
Enable bandit check for password_config_option_not_marked_secret

The password_config_option_not_marked_secret was not enabled and it
didn't pass because it considered the [auth] password config option
to be a password option that wasn't set to secret when it's actually
just the plugin for the password.

Enable the check and mark the [auth] password config option as not
a security issue. This will help us catch new password config
options that aren't marked as secret, which has been a common
issue.

commit_message:
Add auth version for legacy OpenStack clients

Adding this environment variable expands Identity v3 coverage for legacy
OpenStack CLI clients. This corrects the authentication URLs used even
if v2 is still being used.

Change-Id: I68197ffd12d71a437c482f13520b83cb08d4c9de
Closes-Bug: #1495685

commit_message:
Adds the config_template to keystone

The change modifies the keystone template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I957d55df81c7edd4e2a95597a62a75c6bd0f46fe

commit_message:
Adds the config_template to glance

The change modifies the glance template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I13fc6f38679267a84104cae948517d185e9f4ece

commit_message:
adds the config_template to pip_lock_down

The change modifies the pip_lock_down template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I620b7f599a9e41f5fe38a2d038b53cfa227c1d55

commit_message:
adds the config_template to galera_server

The change modifies the galera_server template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I6f34dff6e3a8ab8d2aad6a413b9a59f325c1be7b

commit_message:
Add filter to secret list for acl secrets

Adds a ACL only filter when getting the list of secrets. If
'http://barbican:9311/v1/secrets/acl_only=true' is given then
the list of secrets returned should only contain secrets that the
user is on the ACL for (regardless of project).
If acl_only is false or is not given, then
the default project based behaviour will be used.

DocImpact
APIImpact
Change-Id: I8e511d29b77ce15d2000ee2876a12cf6a95771c6
Closes-Bug: #1459780

[{'created': '2015-09-21 13:43:04.000000000', 'message': 'ErrorsFactory returns only defined errors

ErrorsFactory had __getattr__ method that was used to always
return any error (if it doesn't existed, it created a new one).
This was causing "hasattr" to return 'True' for every check.
Due to this any code, that wanted to check for some unique attributes
in ErrorsFactory was working incorrectly. This was the case for
a py.test library when scannig code when looking for tests.
Now this behavior has been removed. This uncovered new bugs
which was fixed.

Change-Id: I3c9be96dbcc535ea9c730d29b065479cc318fd9f
Closes-Bug: #1497664
(cherry picked from commit 9757292c3b7f2a8d955fbe2cc1673a2baac702e5)
'}]
commit_message:
ErrorsFactory returns only defined errors

ErrorsFactory had __getattr__ method that was used to always
return any error (if it doesn't existed, it created a new one).
This was causing "hasattr" to return 'True' for every check.
Due to this any code, that wanted to check for some unique attributes
in ErrorsFactory was working incorrectly. This was the case for
a py.test library when scannig code when looking for tests.
Now this behavior has been removed. This uncovered new bugs
which was fixed.

Change-Id: I3c9be96dbcc535ea9c730d29b065479cc318fd9f
Closes-Bug: #1497664
(cherry picked from commit 9757292c3b7f2a8d955fbe2cc1673a2baac702e5)

commit_message:
Adds the config_template to heat

The change modifies the heat template tasks such that it's now
using the config_template action plugin. This change will make so that
config files can be dynamically updated, by a deployer, at run time,
without requiring the need to modify the in tree templates or defaults.

Partially implements: blueprint tunable-openstack-configuration

Change-Id: I53bb46f19fd61a5b320dbf0650433c5dd93b98fe

commit_message:
Remove Cisco-specific neutron client commands

Removed Cisco-specific neutron client commands and ported
code to networking-cisco as part of phase 2 of core vendor
decompostion.

Corresponding vendor repo change: Ia93134bfc7379781e56b0494087e3eca3fd9b232

Partial-Bug: #1490768
Partial-implements: blueprint core-vendor-decomposition

Change-Id: I97d1370e2a3333fbcf87107f4624590d43d2940d

commit_message:
Don't always load client

This change load client only when a command requires it.

This avoid to connect to API is not needed and avoid the
auth plugin to ask something, if the user just request help.

Change-Id: I4e184f8ce45c137fdcda77ab95d42b4e695b321d

commit_message:
Add tox targets for functional testing on 2 and 3

Previously, the functional tests would run using the `python` in your
environment, which was 3 for myself and 2 for most others. We should
really be testing on both versions as we do for unit tests. A change to
the gate will follow this.

Change-Id: I2bd2664018c135593a96fd6ba5741279da772e76
Closes-Bug: 1489935

Move resize claim abort test to test_tracker

Moves the unit test for resize claim abort from test_resource_tracker to
test_tracker and NoDBTestCase.

commit_message:
Validate node group exists when assigning node groups to nodes

API validator checks for existence of a node group. In the case
where a specified group does not exist it returns the proper status
code and error message.

Change-Id: I58ae9094046e5f261839ec90eaac79e639dbfb4d
Closes-bug: #1494835

Update several of our libs for their final pre-stable branch releases
for liberty.

commit_message:
Clean up line continuation in Storwize driver

There are multiple places in the Storwize driver where '\' is used
for line  continuation. This patch replaces '\' with '()' to make
the code consistent.

Change-Id: Ic64f0562f1e25e499c4fecd366998e31e8ebee7a

commit_message:
Add missing dependency repository for Liberty for EL

There are three repositories for liberty in entreprise
linux:
- delorean
- delorean-liberty-testing
- delorean-common-testing

This commit adds the two missing ones so that delorean
can pull the proper dependencies. Otherwise, it might
have either broken dependencies or outdated ones from EPEL.

Change-Id: Ia815b38d3a83a89c582ea874e39c170d618b99e5
Closes-Bug: #1497436

commit_message:
Regression: git is required to build from source on ubuntu

- this change fixes a regression of bug/1481560
- this change re-adds git to the openstack base image
  when building images from source on ubuntu.
- removed explicit git install from kolla-ansible

Closes-Bug: #1496561
Change-Id: Ia8a125e40bc6510af6d44c5317647be7ce27b0d6

commit_message:
mark deprecated ceilometer items

this patch:
- adds note that ceilometer-polling is the recommended service to
  use when polling compute, central, or ipmi data.
- marks db2nosql driver as deprecated as it is not longer developed
  by ibm.
- mark RPC publisher as deprecated for notifier publisher.

Change-Id: I34838dd17c681cae0fa360f8648434f3d777323f

commit_message:
Change roles to rules in policy.json file

Each role should be assigned exactly one to a rule, and only the rule
should be used thereafter in the policy.json file.  For consistency,
I also remove _role as a suffix for rule names.

Change-Id: I412a2516690b3be622c9cf7e0a959e8a796b1923
Closes-bug: #1497646

commit_message:
Make 'alarm_history_time_to_live' parameter configurable

alarm_history_time_to_live is new ceilometer parameter:
http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/ceilometer-specs/specs/liberty/delete-alarmhistory.html

Make time_to_live parameter deprecated in favor of metering_time_to_live

Change-Id: Ifd16853779101202c4d6ea5a7237aeceeb0ade7c

Add barbican to Chapter1
  (for CLI Ref)

commit_message:
Update path to subunit2html in post_test_hook

Per:

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-August/072982.html

The location of subunit2html changed on the images in the gate
so update the path used in the post_test_hook.

Long-term we should just use what's in devstack-gate.

Change-Id: I5e50e7d7ad845aba26403df1df412c0a139a6dc7
Closes-Bug: #1491646
(cherry picked from commit 3e862bbb1e2a7b488cf2de43651270e6afbb82ad)

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be

commit_message:
Remove lib-forward-testing from Designate Client

Designate Client is not installed as part of stock
devstack, so this job hasn't been testing anything.

In addition, a recent DevStack addition to valdidate
all libs-from-git are correctly installed now causes
this job to fail every time.

Change-Id: I5d22fe0e209265475c24e4c620e2fa2a4bcfd4ec

commit_message:
Remove now useless build_url method

Since we url keystoneauth we don't really need
a method to build the URL, this one is now static.

The keystoneauth Adapter is reponsible to and the url prefix.

Replace keystoneclient by keystoneauth1

keystoneclient session will be removed in the futur in
favor of keystoneauth1.

This change replace keystoneclient by keystoneauth1.

Change-Id: I1c411ef73b83ed7f904c416bc8f45abf35b5a168

commit_message:
Handle unquoted node names from virt types

Not all virt types return node names in quotations when requesting a list of running VMs.
This should not be a requirement by the code, so relax this restriction and match
node names without quotes.

Also, add comments to clarify the expected return value for each of the commands.

Change-Id: I55a259f8687627a4ebd2d8bb941eb5b1041045c7
Closes-Bug: #1496867

[Intern] New --no-nailgun-start option for run_tests.sh

This option allows to skip starting of nailgun which could speed
up debugging UI functional tests

when doing direct OVS plugging.

commit_message:
Rename neutron-powervm to networking-powervm

As part of the changes outlined here:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/206658/
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/206662/

Rename neutron-powervm to use the networking-powervm namespace in
accordance with the Neutron Stadium effort.

Change-Id: I445f89b5781647671f2e4daf38a7b60bc58cb686

commit_message:
Log the SHA1 hash of X-Auth-Token value

Don't log sensitive information like the token value from
X-Auth-Token. Instead, we log the sha1 hash of the token value,
prefixed by '{SHA1}'.

This is the convention used within OpenStack, so that the token
can be tracked through different services.

E.g: keystone use pki provider, the token is very long, log in
token too long.

Change-Id: I6633fa0eda25d994a32d26019cf62ac1d4f760df
Closes-bug: #1429701

commit_message:
Fix few typos in headings

1.) Corrected headings according to rules of migrations by
placing "=======" on headings in the files
2.) Some headings have extra "====", they are removed
3.) Launchpad url have '~' which makes error: page not found
,so it is removed

Change-Id: I99581025d579f18da9ebe57267fb002cbcba28dd

commit_message:
Close backend connections in tests

Tests creates connections to backends that we need to explicitly close
so that they don't pile up. This adds new methods to drivers,
implementation on the various backends, and cleanup calls in tests to do
so.

Change-Id: I48fb31f21403d5af56b13979eb8710cbf42948e4

commit_message:
Fix ca related controllers

GET /cas/ would return all the CAs even if they're not in the project.
This CR enables the behavior in which if project CAs are defined, then
it will show them when running GET /cas/; If they're not, then it will
show all CAs.

On the other hand, this fixes an issue with remove-from-project. Where
if you would remove the last CA from a project, it would still have a
preferred one. So the behavior now is:
If the user tries to delete the preferred CA; an error will be returned
unless it is the last CA left for the project.

Change-Id: I195ecc4ea6a8748e003fd17b219a727701e5e15d

This was causing "hasattr" to return 'True' for every check.
Due to this any code, that wanted to check for some unique attributes
in ErrorsFactory was working incorrectly. This was the case for
a py.test library when scannig code when looking for tests.

commit_message:
ErrorsFactory returns only defined errors

ErrorsFactory had __getattr__ method that was used to always
return any error (if it doesn't existed, it created a new one).
This was causing "hasattr" to return 'True' for every check.
Due to this any code, that wanted to check for some unique attributes
in ErrorsFactory was working incorrectly. This was the case for
a py.test library when scannig code when looking for tests.
Now this behavior has been removed. This uncovered new bugs
which was fixed.

Change-Id: I3c9be96dbcc535ea9c730d29b065479cc318fd9f
Closes-Bug: #1497664

commit_message:
retain existing listeners on refresh

there is an overhead to killing and recreating listeners. this patch
keeps the pipeline listeners we already have after rebalancing
rather than blindly killing and recreating all of them.

Change-Id: Ic7c23fd7649ca0b828cc4266582163bd326c2b80
Closes-Bug: #1496459

commit_message:
Remove a TODO item in cluster detach policy

There was a TODO for checking whether there are other actions going on
when detaching a policy from a cluster. A closer examination proved that
this is unlikely to happen because CLUSTER_DETACH_POLICY action itself
is an action that will lock the cluster before getting executed. The
cluster lock already prevents other action from execution in parallel to
the curent one.

Change-Id: Ib786d688a4fe0062e06498fbfaf0c0b37c788c1e

commit_message:
Get 'count' from action.inputs instead of action.data

When doing cluster-scale-in, count number is stored in action.inputs
instead of action.data, deletion_policy should get this value from
correct location.

Closes-Bug: #1497827
Change-Id: Ia01222a884b403a097830c6fa4eafb5cd7625cd3

commit_message:
Rebase HttpError exception initializer

Recent pypowervm changes (branch useful_500_message) removed the 'msg'
argument from the pypowervm.exceptions.HttpError initializer (the
message is now constructed internally from the response).  Rebase on the
change.

Change-Id: I21f0a1de77cc9de43927c3ed18e34a9082a42330

Rebase HttpError exception initializer

Recent pypowervm changes (branch useful_500_message) removed the 'msg'
argument from the pypowervm.exceptions.HttpError initializer (the
message is now constructed internally from the response).  Rebase on the
change.

This also now passes py34 tox.

commit_message:
Rename SwiftScenarioTest to ObjectStorageScenarioTest

This commit renames SwiftScenarioTest to ObjectStorageScenarioTest
because of the consistency. The name of the other scenario test classes
are service name not project name: e.g. Network, Baremetal, etc.

Change-Id: I701b9ba9fda536b50b2fcbf6922f0b64f6404bf7

py3: Fix python34 check job

Replace dict.iteritems() with six.iteritems(dict) to support
Python 2 and Python 3.

In case of delete operation, we can ignore key not found
DB exceptions as the key is being deleted anyway

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-09-20 04:59:04.000000000', 'message': 'Add Dragonflow exceptions for common DB exceptions

Dragonflow support pluggable DB solutions, however the client code
(Neutron plugin, local controller) might need to use specific
exceptions, for example "Key Not Found exception".
This allows the client to map between the DB solutions exceptions
and the exceptions Dragonflow expect to catch.

Change-Id: Ia2f81243986dd13938b5f94d9e9bac216f39e054
'}]
commit_message:
Add Dragonflow exceptions for common DB exceptions

Dragonflow support pluggable DB solutions, however the client code
(Neutron plugin, local controller) might need to use specific
exceptions, for example "Key Not Found exception".
This allows the client to map between the DB solutions exceptions
and the exceptions Dragonflow expect to catch.

Change-Id: Ia2f81243986dd13938b5f94d9e9bac216f39e054

commit_message:
Add PRODUCTION: docker into fuelmenu default settings

This variable is going to be used by puppet to find
out if it is run on a server or it is just a part of
the ISO build process. This patch is a part of
version.yaml deprecation plan.

Change-Id: Ic906c571e51e53ff962ac28e0ce453c42ded1166
Implements: bp docker-images-perestroika

[{'created': '2015-09-20 18:59:27.000000000', 'message': 'Function caller was incorrect when called from Parallel block

Current instruction is tracked as a value in yaql context.
But in Parallel block individual instructions executed in separate
threads. As a result when those threads get scheduled current
instruction in caller context already changes to the last one
(which is a synchronization point for the Parallel block).

To solve this all spawned threads need to work in their own
dedicated child contexts. Then each of those contexts will have
its own "current instruction". However this also brings a side effect:
all local variable modifications made by spawned threads will
be go to those new contexts and will be lost upon exit from Parallel.
To solve this context that local variable need to be in is marked with
special flag. When executing "$var: value" expressions DSL will scan
context chain up to the context with that flag. Currently the only
context with the flag is a method context that defines local variable scope.

Change-Id: I0647915c104dfe4e00dd86c17726245d1bbc3beb
Closes-Bug: #1497772

commit_message:
Function caller was incorrect when called from Parallel block

Current instruction is tracked as a value in yaql context.
But in Parallel block individual instructions executed in separate
threads. As a result when those threads get scheduled current
instruction in caller context already changes to the last one
(which is a synchronization point for the Parallel block).

To solve this all spawned threads need to work in their own
dedicated child contexts. Then each of those contexts will have
its own "current instruction". However this also brings a side effect:
all local variable modifications made by spawned threads will
be go to those new contexts and will be lost upon exit from Parallel.
To solve this context that local variable need to be in is marked with
special flag. When executing "$var: value" expressions DSL will scan
context chain up to the context with that flag. Currently the only
context with the flag is a method context that defines local variable scope.

Change-Id: I0647915c104dfe4e00dd86c17726245d1bbc3beb
Closes-Bug: #1497772

commit_message:
Temporarily pins to unblock gating

This also addresses an issue in the openstackclient where the tagged
version has a neutron client version dependency which is unresolvable
without the client entry being presnet to allow the repo infra to
index the requirements.

Version 2.0.0 of the django openstack auth package was recently
released and causes session backed with mysql for horizon to fail a
DB sync.

Change-Id: Icd18f77e2b1525d4769c3df604030e7aa73917f3

commit_message:
Add additional memcache configuration options

This change adds the ability to specify the dead retry, socket timeout,
pool max size, and pool unused timeout for the memcache and cache
configuration options

Change-Id: I45c2fc540ef39f36b46a2aeaeac56fe9698c0f41
Closes-Bug: 1488551

commit_message:
Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

When logging is already set up, it can be useful to disable this option
to avoid logs duplication (collected by Upstart, for example)

Change-Id: I9b71528de3aaba2323e17ea67d5457e3ba6d288a
Related-bug: #1482564
(cherry picked from commit 4d749f5abfe13b8ff5f2919d8dce6ff8f499f35e)

commit_message:
WIP: Add support for new parameters in generic backend

- 'service_instance_user',
- 'service_instance_password',
- 'service_instance_flavor_id' and
- 'service_network_cidr'

!! Need to implement acceptance test !!

Change-Id: I335b87dff88af735a14232d3a3d1a670d8316fb9
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Stop building ironic-discoverd

It isn't hosted on the same gerrit as tripleo so we shouldn't
be including it in the projects we build. Instead we should just
rely on whats in the trunk repository we happen to be using.

Change-Id: I9513ad60f32af28ef7821974749aede443be858d

commit_message:
Initial msync run for all Puppet OpenStack modules

This patch is the initial modulesync run, it impacts:

* gitignore: just a sync between projects
* gemfile:
  - update and allow to setup facter version and gem source
  - split beaker gems with a dedicated group
  - switch to rspec-puppet 2.2.0
* rakefile:
  - use the new syntax for lint configuration
  - add a acceptance target
* acceptance:
  - sync nodesets
* spec: added rspec coverage report

Change-Id: I05e2e4c13bd264c65fad8bade1886e23a50184d9

commit_message:
Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

When logging is already set up, it can be useful to disable this option
to avoid logs duplication (collected by Upstart, for example)

Change-Id: I07444d0344ef479d414dbeac6a50327d8e632b26
Closes-bug: #1482564
(cherry picked from commit 4190d9d10888ac8025a5e0a366c5bbb0a975db0a)

subject: Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

commit_message:
Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

When logging is already set up, it can be useful to disable this option
to avoid logs duplication (collected by Upstart, for example)

Change-Id: I07444d0344ef479d414dbeac6a50327d8e632b26
Closes-bug: #1482564
(cherry picked from commit 4190d9d10888ac8025a5e0a366c5bbb0a975db0a)

[{'created': '2015-09-21 09:12:06.000000000', 'message': 'Fix .coveragrc to prevent nose tests error

Since v4.0 the coverage package raises an error if unrecognized
options are found in .coveragrc [1]. Previously they were ignored. The
ignore-errors option therefore causes nosetests with coverage to error
because the option should be ignore_errors (underscore not hyphen).

[1] https://bitbucket.org/ned/coveragepy/src/tip/CHANGES.rst

Change-Id: Ic488801b7cc43217f9e2a4ed945e06505b667608
'}]
commit_message:
Fix .coveragrc to prevent nose tests error

Since v4.0 the coverage package raises an error if unrecognized
options are found in .coveragrc [1]. Previously they were ignored. The
ignore-errors option therefore causes nosetests with coverage to error
because the option should be ignore_errors (underscore not hyphen).

[1] https://bitbucket.org/ned/coveragepy/src/tip/CHANGES.rst

Change-Id: Ic488801b7cc43217f9e2a4ed945e06505b667608

commit_message:
Devref: Document why conductor has a task api/manager

In addition to being a database proxy and object backporter the
conductor also manages rebuild, resize/migrate, and building instances.
This documents why that is done.

Change-Id: Ieb9134302d21a11fe9b9ee876bb7b0dd32b437e1

commit_message:
Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

When logging is already set up, it can be useful to disable this option
to avoid logs duplication (collected by Upstart, for example)

Change-Id: I07444d0344ef479d414dbeac6a50327d8e632b26
Closes-bug: #1482564
(cherry picked from commit 4190d9d10888ac8025a5e0a366c5bbb0a975db0a)

commit_message:
Add keystoneclient to test-requirements

The auth parameter name validation requires keystoneclient and can't be
tested if it's not there.

While we're at it - update the current requirements to be inline with
global requirements.

Change-Id: I6da62476f3851670545143184f9f29479f1caaca

commit_message:
Add an ability to manage use_stderr parameter

When logging is already set up, it can be useful to disable this option
to avoid logs duplication (collected by Upstart, for example)

Change-Id: I9b71528de3aaba2323e17ea67d5457e3ba6d288a
Related-bug: #1482564
(cherry picked from commit 4d749f5abfe13b8ff5f2919d8dce6ff8f499f35e)

[{'account_id': 18418, 'date': '2015-09-16 01:39:33.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 10068, 'date': '2015-09-16 01:39:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

commit_message:
Require at least 4.2.0 of stdlib

This module passes two arguments to the ensure_packages() function
provided by stdlib. Until 4.2.0 the function only allowed one
argument for the package name(s), so we require at least this version
to work.

Change-Id: Ib5b1d0b3f07c0a964ff25031e349e0c0e1aa8513

commit_message:
Validate cluster in node group creation

Currently if user pass incorrect or invalid cluster ID to nodegroup
creation POST request the 500 Internal Server error is occur. That's
not the way we should handle invalid input data. Let's throw
404 Not Found if invalid cluster ID is passed.

Closes-Bug: #1494320

Change-Id: Ief3754367690c83021f1e636f58311f0c02c941a
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

[{'created': '2015-09-14 09:11:40.000000000', 'message': 'Add string freeze to Common Cycle with milestones

commit_message:
Mentions the governance/../extra-atcs file

Currently the section about elections makes no mention of the
extra-atcs governance file and when it is to be used.

This patch adds a sentence or two to prompt those with the use
case to look at the file and inquire further should they need.

Change-Id: I33e6fc66f8df844ccd69dbbc886f9b403f161fc0

commit_message:
Add review notes to the readme

We need to document general guidelines for reviewing release requests.

This is following the recent gate breakage with oslo.utils 1.4.1.

The intent here is mostly for the special cases which impact stable branches,
but the semver reminder is important for non-stable branches also since
improper versioning on master where semver wasn't followed, e.g. incrementing
a patch version when the minor version should have been updated, has led to
a lot of the problems we see with stable branches.

Related-Bug: #1496650

Change-Id: I4c7013e265bb533dbac2c8804dea01dacff5de4b

commit_message:
Repairing disable_terminate and shutdown_terminate flags

Add two new attributes to the Servers Extended Attributes (OS-EXT-SRV-ATTR)
extension: disable_terminate (boolean) and shutdown_terminate (boolean).
Get them supported in POST, PUT and GET methods to allow creation,
modification and information retrieval accordingly.
Change the policy for the extension from rule:admin_api to
rule:admin_or_owner.
All of the internal mechanisms are already in place and functional. Only
API exposure is required.

Spec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/189334/

Change-Id: I43c74da0b0b8706e95375d97f834fdf0d337af46
Implements: blueprint server-termination-behavior
